                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">The front and back cover are stamped with gold crosses in the center and decorative designs around the edges. The protection quire shows imprints of tooled leather, suggesting that this manuscript was originally bound in a tooled leather cover and then rebound in its present stamped vinyl cover</decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d2"> Decorative designs: <locus target="#1r #54r #87r #146r"/> (haräg);
                    multiple full stops are used as section dividers throughout</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc>
                             Many characteristics of the manuscript make it clear that it was produced in the government scriptorium: the green leather cover, the trimmed text block, the distinctive harags, etc
                           </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                          <locus target="#ir(ecto) #iv(erso) #iir(ecto) #iiv(erso) #iiir(ecto) #iiiv(erso) #ivr(ecto) #ivv(erso) #vr(ecto) #vv(erso) #vir(ecto) #viv(erso) #viir(ecto) #viiv(erso) #viiir(ecto) #viiiv(erso) #ixr(ecto) #ixv(erso) #xr(ecto) #xv(erso) #xir(ecto) #xiv(erso) #xiir(ecto) #193v #194r #194v #195r #195v #196r #196v #197r #197v #198r #198v #199r #199v #200r #200v #201r #201v #202r #202v #203r #203v #204r"/>
                           <desc>
                              blank
                            </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                          <locus target="#192v"/>
                           <desc>
                              An extensive colophon mentions the names of the members of the royal household and the names of the thirteen bishops installed by the first patriarch of Ethiopia, <persName ref="PRS2533Baselyos"/>
                           </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <desc type="ScribalNoteCommissioning">
                             The manuscript was commissioned by Abba Ḥana (treasurer of the palace). The scribe’s name is Habtä Mikae’l of Sälale
                           </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <desc>
                             Identified in the insurance hand list as Liturgical 18
                           </desc>
                        </item>
